main event: An observer reported seeing a bright light in the sky, which disappeared behind some trees and could not be located again.
interesting points: The light was of unknown origin and did not pulsate or blink., The observation lasted approximately ten seconds., The observer's parents first noticed the object before calling the observer's attention to it., The angle of observation was noted to be 10 degrees above the horizon, heading South Southeast., The investigator found no corroborating evidence or photographs despite thorough inquiries.
sighted object: a bright light in the sky
witness description: The observer is a student at the University of Nebraska with some knowledge of sky phenomena.
